    <summary>CMake module for C/C++ projects with predefined standard structure</summary>
    <description>
abcmake is a CMake module that simplifies building C/C++ projects with a predefined standard structure. It provides automatic component discovery, linking, and installation features.

## Features

- Automatic discovery and building of components in a structured project
- Registry for linking components by name rather than path
- Auto-detection of vendored CMake packages
- Generates compile_commands.json
- Install step for each built target
- Single-file distributable

## Usage

Add to your CMakeLists.txt:

```cmake
find_package(abcmake REQUIRED)
add_main_component(${PROJECT_NAME})
```

## Project Structure

```
project/
├── CMakeLists.txt
├── src/
│   └── main.cpp
├── include/
│   └── project/
└── components/
    └── mylib/
        ├── CMakeLists.txt
        ├── src/
        └── include/
```
